<p>Akaki Tsereteli State University is a well-known higher education institution located in the city of Kutaisi, Georgia. The university was established in 1930 and is named after the famous Georgian poet, Akaki Tsereteli. The university has a long history of providing quality education in a variety of fields, including medicine, humanities, social sciences, natural sciences, and law.</p>

<h3>Mission and Vision:</h3>
<p>The mission of Akaki Tsereteli State University is to provide students with a quality education that is relevant and up-to-date with the latest developments in their field. The university aims to create an environment that fosters creativity, critical thinking, and research, enabling students to become knowledgeable and productive members of society. The vision of the university is to be recognized as a leading institution in Georgia that provides world-class education to its students.</p>
<!-- <p>The history of Akaki Tsereteli State University started eight decades ago and now, it is a higher educational institution in Georgia distinguished with its excellent traditions, which have found a decent place in the cultural-intellectual and moral upbringing of generations. The University has gained universal recognition as a result of staff training, high quality scientific potential and wide- ranging links with scientific institutes of advanced countries.</p>
<p>Kutaisi Akaki Tsereteli State University, in fact, was founded in the entrails of Ivane Javakhishvili Tbilisi State University. In July 1930, the authorities abolished Tbilisi State University and created four independent higher education institutions at its base. One of them was the State Pedagogical Institute, which, from then on, until 1933, was functioning in Tbilisi. In 1933, the institute continued functioning in Kutaisi from February 13 of the same year. In 1933-1990 the institution was in the position of Alexander Tsulukidze State Pedagogical Institute.</p> -->
<h3>Faculty and Programs:</h3>
<p><b>The university has a total of 7 faculties, offering undergraduate and graduate programs in various disciplines. The faculties are as follows:</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>Faculty of Humanities</li>
  <li>Faculty of Law and Social Sciences</li>
  <li>Faculty of Education Sciences</li>
  <li>Faculty of Exact and Natural Sciences</li>
  <li>Faculty of Medicine</li>
  <li>Faculty of Agrarian Sciences and Forestry</li>
  <li>Faculty of Engineering and Technology</li>
  </ul>
  <p>The Faculty of Medicine at Akaki Tsereteli State University is well known for providing quality medical education to students from all over the world. The faculty offers a six-year program in Medicine that leads to the degree of Doctor of Medicine (MD). The program is taught in English and is approved by the Georgian Ministry of Education and Science and the World Health Organization (WHO).</p>

  <h3>Facilities:</h3>
  <p>The university provides its students with modern facilities, including lecture halls, laboratories, libraries, and a well-equipped hospital where students can get hands-on clinical training. The campus also has several sports facilities, including a gym, a football field, and a basketball court, to ensure students have a well-rounded experience while studying at the university.</p>



<h3>Admission and Fees:</h3>

<p>Admission to Akaki Tsereteli State University is based on the results of the Unified National Examinations, a test that is taken by students after completing their secondary education. The university also accepts international students, and they are required to submit their academic transcripts and other necessary documents to be considered for admission.</p>
<p>The tuition fees for international students studying medicine at Akaki Tsereteli State University are quite affordable compared to other medical schools in Europe or the United States. The total tuition fee for the six-year MD program is around $30,000.</p>

